{
  "text": "1. HBeAg-positive chronic hepatitis (Table 8 ) -In one phase II trial, 155 a higher percent of patients who received pegIFN-\u2423 had HBeAg seroconversion compared to those who received standard IFN-\u2423. In a subsequent phase III trial, 814 patients were randomized to receive pegIFN-\u24232a 180 mcg weekly, pegIFN-\u24232a 180 mcg weekly \u03e9 lamivudine 100 mg daily, or lamivudine 100 mg daily for 48 weeks. [CITATION_1] At the end of treatment, viral suppression was most marked in the group that received combination therapy. Despite differences in the degree of viral suppression, HBeAg seroconversion was similar in the three groups at the end of treatment: 27%, 24%, and 20%, respectively, but significantly higher in the two groups that received pegIFN-\u2423 when response was assessed 24 weeks after treatment was stopped: 32%, 27%, and 19%, respectively. These data indicate that pegIFN\u24232a monotherapy was superior to lamivudine monotherapy in inducing sustained HBeAg seroconversion, and comparable to combination therapy of pegIFN-\u24232a and lamivudine.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "40360381"
